<br>
HOWEVER, I don't think you're taking the right approach here, except for Ling perhaps, who has been trying for a while now. In fact trying forever.<br>
<br>
If you want Dain dead, if you want your epics, if you want any of this stuff...then USE the SGA as it is meant to be used. It's an alliance for us so that we don't have to forsake our family-style guilds with real newbies and a sense of community and loyalty for the sake of the &quot;ultimate&quot; end game. The SGA is us, all of us, in all the guilds. We have the potential to be an amazing &quot;force&quot; in the world of Norrath for all of you who care about that...<br>
<br>
By this I mean, stop moping around that Hareq isn't here to organize something and do it yourselves. The crises of leadership in a game like this is that it destroys alot of the fun. The answer is to share the burden of that responsibility. No one person can handle it, but we all can a little at a time. Work with the SGA, track down the members in your level range, organize stuff...<br>
<br>
Look, I'm not on that much and I'm not high enough to help you that much--Velk Mondays is about all I can promise, but if we each take a little bit, the road will be smoother.<br>
<br>
Whoa Olayv, just read that.<br>
