<br>
I said this before and I will state it again. The number one rule in a multigroup raid is to &quot;SHUT UP!!&quot; Unless you have something important to add, just be quiet!! The second rule is you will die alot, get little exp, get little plat, and only have a small chance of a nice item; so dont whine about any of this stuff!!! The third rule is support the raid leader even if he or she screws up and you all get killed. It is very difficult to run raids and people not holding to the above rules have managed to burn out; Hareq, Zenknight, and every other person willing to lead planes raids for SGA. SGA has very few raids now because the Bitching and Moaning of the &quot;Loot Whores&quot; has chased our leaders away.<br>
<br>
About us using ooc to communicate: I dont recall any problems from others about this. Ooc is a standard &quot;accepted&quot; way to communicate during raids. Everyone with much experience on multi-group raids know this and it is never been a problem to my knowledge. Some newbie to planes and multi groups raids might complain but normally the rest of the zone tells them to &quot;SHUT UP!&quot; I did seventeen levels in Sol B, and FG and Naggy raids happened all the time. They always seemed to use ooc and it was just accepted that that is the way it is. Any newbie that bitched was soon slapped down by others in the zone not even on the raid. That is just the way it is in EQ. It would be nice if they coded a way to set up a raid chat channel, but they havent so we use occ.<br>
<br>
I am sorry if anyone feels that SGA is not doing for them what they feel it should. My question is; what have you done for SGA? If you want to raid the planes then start leading multi-group raids, gain experience at it and a good reputation; then you can lead a planes raid for SGA. If you cant handle leading raids, then you best support those that do!! Dont Bitch!! Dont moan!! Just do your best to help those under all the pressure of leading raids.<br>
<br>
Although I have lead over 20 raids and events for my guild and SGA, I will not lead a planes raid. There are two many people that go on those raids that are not ready to do so. They are either too low in level, or are too fixated on loot. The amount a bitching and moaning on a planes raid is overwhelming on the leader who has more than enough to do already.<br>
<br>
Myriah<br>
<br>
P.S. Good luck Anmesty!! I hope you survive is rocky time and come out stronger then before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unayl7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nayl7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/13/01 8:46:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Alliance</span><hr size=1> Echo is not a member of the SGA, though we hope to be someday.  The entire reason for our interest in this organization is exactly what Bamil and Vaiine have said above.  <br>
<br>
At one point, early in our history, we were offered the option of joining a much larger guild.  We declined, because we formed this guild out of a sense of friendship and family as much as anything else.  Yes, we want to do the large scale, upper end part of the game.  Yes, we want the phat lewtz.  But we want to do this with the friends we have made along the way.  We view the SGA as a unique opportunity to reach these goals, as we make a lot of new friends and go places with them we could not go alone.  <br>
<br>
I see in the other comments above concerns about things like a lack of a guild channel for coordinating raids, and more seriously, favoritism in distributing loot.  I regard both of these as issues that can be dealt with so long as we all agree to work at them.  The reason guilds work is because the people in them know, respect and like each other, and willingly forgive mistakes and screw-ups because that is what families and friends do for each other.  <br>
<br>
I cannot say that I know everyone in every guild in the SGA as well as I know the members of Echo.  But I can say that from what I have seen so far, I would like to.<br>
<br>
Nayl Nightglade<br>
52nd Emerald Warrior<br>
Echo of Valor <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showMessage?topicID=260.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showMessage?topicID=262.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=255.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.threadControl?topicID=255.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=255.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=255.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="saryrnguildallianceboardfrm1">General Discussion<option value="saryrnguildallianceboardfrm8">Guild Links<option value="saryrnguildallianceboardfrm4">Alliance Events<option value="saryrnguildallianceboardfrm2